# 🧠 BrainUp – AI Email Sequence Generator

> Automatically generate personalized cold outreach emails from CRM data using AI.

## Why I Built This

When prospecting manually, I quickly encountered the same problems:

* Writing every email from scratch was time-consuming.
* Generic templates produced poor response rates.
* Personalization wasn't scalable.
* Tracking where each prospect was in the outreach sequence became difficult.

I wanted a system capable of producing **high-quality, personalized drafts** while keeping full control over what gets sent.

Instead of automatically emailing prospects, this workflow generates **reviewable Gmail drafts**. This human validation step reduces the risk of AI mistakes while saving several hours every week.

---

# The Problem

Cold outreach often fails because businesses either:

* send the exact same email to everyone;
* spend too much time personalizing every message;
* lose track of follow-ups;
* stop following up after the first email.

This workflow solves those problems by combining a CRM, AI and workflow automation.

---

# How It Works

```text
Schedule (Weekdays 08:00)
        │
        ▼
Read prospects from Airtable CRM
        │
        ▼
Filter eligible prospects
        │
        ▼
Determine outreach stage
        │
        ▼
Generate personalized email with GPT
        │
        ▼
Create Gmail Draft
        │
        ▼
Update CRM stage
```

---

# Workflow Overview

### 1. Trigger

The workflow can be started:

* automatically every weekday at **08:00**
* manually for testing purposes

---

### 2. Read CRM

Prospects are retrieved from Airtable.

For every record, the workflow extracts information such as:

* Full name
* Company
* Website
* Internal notes
* Sales angles
* Current sequence step
* Response status

---

### 3. Prospect Validation

Only prospects matching the following criteria continue:

* valid email address
* no previous reply
* sequence not completed
* valid CRM record

Invalid or completed prospects are ignored.

---

### 4. AI Personalization

The workflow builds a structured prompt containing:

* company information
* website
* CRM notes
* outreach context
* current email stage

Depending on the sequence step, the prospect is routed to one of four dedicated AI agents.

---

## Email 1

First contact.

Goal:

* introduce BrainUp
* identify the agency's activities
* explain the value proposition
* ask permission to send a customized visual

---

## Email 2

Follow-up.

Goal:

* send the personalized BrainUp visual
* explain how BrainUp fits existing processes
* invite the prospect to a short meeting

This is the only email that automatically attaches a document stored in Google Drive.

---

## Email 3

Value reminder.

Goal:

Show a concrete business case explaining how poor follow-up can cause lost opportunities and how BrainUp addresses that issue.

---

## Email 4

Final follow-up.

Goal:

Politely close the conversation while giving the prospect one final opportunity to respond.

---

# Gmail Integration

Instead of sending emails automatically, the workflow creates **drafts**.

This allows:

* human review
* final edits
* attachment verification
* spam prevention

No email is sent without approval.

---

# CRM Synchronization

After a draft is created successfully, the workflow:

* increments the outreach stage;
* updates Airtable;
* prepares the next follow-up.

Updates are grouped into batches to reduce Airtable API requests.

---

# AI Model

Current model:

* GPT-4.1 Mini

The AI returns structured JSON containing:

* selected template
* email subject
* email body
* internal reasoning summary

---

# Technologies

* n8n
* Airtable
* OpenAI API
* Gmail API
* Google Drive API
* JavaScript

---

# Why Drafts Instead of Automatic Sending?

This was a deliberate design choice.

While fully automated outreach is possible, keeping a human validation step provides several advantages:

* avoids AI hallucinations;
* catches personalization mistakes;
* reduces accidental emails;
* maintains quality control;
* keeps the sender responsible for every message.

The workflow optimizes writing—not decision-making.

---

# Current Limitations

This workflow intentionally does **not**:

* send emails automatically;
* detect positive or negative replies;
* stop sequences automatically after a reply;
* optimize send time;
* perform A/B testing;
* enrich missing CRM data;
* scrape company websites;
* generate attachments dynamically.

These capabilities belong to separate workflows.

---

# Future Improvements

Planned features include:

* reply detection
* sentiment analysis
* automatic sequence interruption
* CRM scoring
* adaptive email timing
* multi-language generation
* automatic company research
* performance analytics
* response-rate dashboard

---

# Business Impact

This automation reduces the repetitive work involved in B2B prospecting by:

* generating personalized outreach in seconds;
* ensuring every prospect follows the correct sequence;
* keeping CRM data synchronized;
* reducing manual copy/paste;
* allowing sales teams to focus on conversations instead of writing emails.

The objective is not to replace salespeople.

It is to eliminate repetitive administrative work so they can spend more time building relationships.

